headlines.description: — Tobias Harris scored 28 points, Tyrese Maxey added 24 and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Dallas Mavericks 120-116 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris and Maxey help Sixers win again without Embiid, beating Doncic's Mavs 120-116

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 29 points, Jayson Tatum had 27 on his 26th birthday, and the NBA-best Boston Celtics posted their third-largest winning margin in franchise history, drubbing the weary Golden State Warriors 140-88 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, Tatum lead Celtics to 3rd-biggest win in franchise history, 140-88 over weary Warriors

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard had 32 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 89-88 on Sunday in a physical and defensive game between two of the top four teams in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kawhi Leonard scores 32 points, Clippers edge Timberwolves 89-88 in physical, defensive game

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 29 points for a second straight game and the Orlando Magic completed a four-game season sweep of the Detroit Pistons with a 113-91 victory on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 29 as the Magic ease past the Pistons 113-91

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored 22 points and matched his season high with 11 assists, RJ Barrett had 23 points and the Toronto Raptors held on to beat Charlotte 111-106 on Sunday night for their seventh consecutive home win over the Hornets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quickley has 22 points and 11 assists as Raptors overcome Barnes' absence to beat Hornets 111-106

events.name: New York Knicks at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — One minute into the game, the New York Knicks had their season flash before their eyes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks overcome losing All-Star Jalen Brunson with bruised knee, regroup to beat Cavaliers 107-98

events.name: Indiana Pacers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 31 points and 12 rebounds to lead the San Antonio Spurs past the Indiana Pacers on 117-105 on Sunday night — and posted a stat line that compared favorably with the two best big men in his team's history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Wembanyama has 31 points, 12 rebounds as Spurs top Pacers 117-105

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 35 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Phoenix Suns 118-110 on Sunday night to take the Western Conference lead, rebounding after blowing a 24-point lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 35 points, Thunder hold off Suns 118-110 to regain top spot in West
